<TITLE> 2 die in lightning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 17 (bdnews24.com)  Two persons died by lightning in Lalmonirhat and Thakurgaon on Saturday morning. The dead are Nishikanta Roy, 57, of Aditmari upazila in Lalmonirhat and Shuruj Hasan, 32, of Thakurgaon Sadr upazila. Lalmonirhat bdnews24.com correspondent reported that Nishikanta of Chandanpat village had died being struck by lightning while his wife, Chokobala Rani, 50, was injured. AHM Mahfuzur Rahman, OC of Aditmari Police Station told bdnews24.com that Nishikanta died as soon as he was hit by lightning at around 8.30am. Thakurgaon correspondent said that Suruj Hasan of Kismat-Tewari village died on the spot when he went out in the drizzle in the morning. bdnews24
